OL,3,CVisually impaired mum told she 'should
OL,4,Cnot have kids' in disability hate crime
OL,6,F"There were quite nasty words that
OL,7,Fwere said, and after awhile it was
OL,8,Fjust a case of turning around and
OL,9,Fsaying 'can you stop, because you
OL,10,Fdon't understand.' She called me a
OL,11,Fsp****c.
OL,13,F"There was no point me reporting it to
OL,14,Fanyone, because no one's going to do
OL,15,Fanything. No one would of stuck up for
OL,16,Fme and said 'yes, I did hear that'."
OL,18,FAlthough Sam tries to not let the hate
OL,19,Ftowards her impairment effect her,
OL,20,Fthere are times when it does create
OL,21,Fdoubt.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/9
