OL,3,CVisually impaired mum told she 'should
OL,4,Cnot have kids' in disability hate crime
OL,6,FJessica Tait, Policy Manager at
OL,7,FDisability Positive, said: "It ends up
OL,8,Fbeing a situation where they don't
OL,9,Ffeel they have a community of support
OL,10,Fbehind them, so they don't want to
OL,11,Freport what's happening to them.
OL,13,F"They perhaps don't realise that they
OL,14,Fhave the option to do that."
OL,16,FRachel Ruffle, from Sale, who became a
OL,17,Fwheelchair user after a spinal cord
OL,18,Finjury, has a 14-year-old daughter
OL,19,Fcalled Amelie.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/9
